data.chText: 乡村（人）的；乡村（人）特色的；淳朴的
data.enText: typical of the country or of country people; simple

data.chText: 充满了乡村魅力的旧农舍
data.enText: an old cottage full of rustic charm
made very simply of rough wood

data.chText: 用粗糙木材搭成的栅栏

data.enText: a person who lives in or comes from the country

simple_means.memory_skill: rust 农村 + ic 某种药 → 乡村的

example: the nightlife of Montmartre awed the unsophisticated tourists

tr: characteristic of the fields or country

value.def: You can use rustic to describe things or people that you approve of because they are simple or unsophisticated in a way that is typical of the countryside.

example.ex: ...the rustic charm of a country lifestyle.
...a half dozen or so wonderfully rustic old log cabins.
example.tran: 大约6个颇具乡土风味的古老的小木屋

value.tran: 乡村的;质朴的;有乡村风味的

value.def: You can refer to someone who comes from the countryside as a rustic if you find their behaviour amusing or very different from that of people who live in towns and cities.

example.ex: ...lots of opera-loving Italian rustics in from the country.
example.tran: 许多从乡下来的热爱歌剧的意大利乡巴佬

partsOfSpeech.dec: rur 农村 + al …的，具有…性质的 → 乡村的
rural 乡村的 + ity 具备某种性质，状况 → 乡村景色
rust 农村 + ic 某种药 → 乡村的
rustic 乡村的 + ate 做，造成，使… → 下乡
